remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKWebpEncoder` is a static class that provides methods to encode pixel data as WebP images.
It supports both single-frame encoding (via `Encode`) and multi-frame animated WebP encoding
(via `EncodeAnimated`).

## Examples

```csharp
// Encode a single pixmap to a file
using var stream = File.OpenWrite("image.webp");
var options = new SKWebpEncoderOptions(SKWebpEncoderCompression.Lossy, 80);
SKWebpEncoder.Encode(stream, pixmap, options);

// Encode multiple frames as an animated WebP
var frames = new SKWebpEncoderFrame[]
{
    new SKWebpEncoderFrame(bitmap1, TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds(100)),
    new SKWebpEncoderFrame(bitmap2, TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds(100)),
};
using var animStream = File.OpenWrite("anim.webp");
SKWebpEncoder.EncodeAnimated(animStream, frames, options);
```
